name: Solstice 2024
summary: In 2024, the summer solstice will occur on June 20th, marking the longest day of the year in the Northern Hemisphere. This year's solstice will be the earliest in over 200 years and the earliest since George Washington was president. Due to the Earth's tilt towards the sun during the summer solstice, the sun will be at its highest point in the sky, resulting in longer daylight hours. The summer solstice is a time of celebration for many cultures and has been marked by rituals and festivals throughout history. This year's early solstice may have implications for weather patterns and temperatures, potentially leading to hotter summer months. However, it also offers an opportunity for individuals to adjust their activities and plans to make the most of the extended daylight.
